Abovegames Apps Privacy Policy for the Child-direct and Families apps
Last updated: 21 Dec 2022
This Privacy Policy explains how Abovegames (“us”, “we”, or “our”) processes your personal data when you use any mobile application ("app", "game") targeted to children and published by "Abovegames" developer in the Google Play store or in the Apple AppStore.
This Privacy Policy is in full compliance with the GDPR in EU, COPPA in the US.
We update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make changes, we notify you by revising the date at the top of the policy and, depending on the specific changes, we provide you with additional notice. We encourage you to review the Privacy Policy whenever you access our apps to stay informed about how we process your personal data and how you can protect your privacy.
Collection of information
Information we collect automatically through the app
We do not collect any
Personal Information
from the Child-direct or Designed for Families apps and games.
Information we get through other sources
If you submit information through our website or email we cannot control type of the info you submit and privacy level of such info. See the following sections to know how we store and process such
Directly-sent Information.
Processing of Directly-sent information
As mentioned above we can get unregulated data and information from the users by email or through the website contact form. Mostly we ignore and do not process any Personal Information from such requests, only analyse some general feedback about our apps, complaints and recommendations to improve quality of our apps. But in special cases, including support requests, accidental purchases, personal data removal requests, any kind of complaints about our apps and service - we can use required Personal Information to resolve an issue and satisfy the user.
Storage of information
We will store your data for as long as necessary in order to provide you with the app or otherwise fulfil the purposes as described above, unless further storage is required in order to establish, exercise or defend a legal claim or to comply with applicable law, including accounting rules.
Your data are deleted or anonymized as soon as it no longer serves one of the above mentioned purposes and in any event no later than three (3) years after your interaction with our apps has ceased.
Sharing of information
We do not disclose any information about you to any third-party services such as advertisements networks or statistics services.
Advertisements
In all our child-direct and families apps we serve
non-personalised
ads only. We do not request and do not use and share your device ID or advertisement ID or IP-address or any other user-specific IDs.
Special cases
If it comes to us attention that Personal Information has been collected from a person under the minimum age limit, we will delete this information as quickly as possible. If you believe that we may have Personal Information from or about a child under the minimum age limit, please contact us at
contact@abovegames.com
.
Parental Access. If you wish to update, correct, or delete the Personal Information that we have for your child, you may do so by contacting us at
contact@abovegames.com
.
If you have additional questions about our privacy practices related to children under the applicable minimum age, please contact us at
contact@abovegames.com
.
